Segmenting Audiences for Security Training
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Implement Python-based audience segmentation for cybersecurity training programs
Categorize employees by role, location, and risk factors
Apply the AIDA (Attention, Interest, Desire, Action) model to create targeted messages
Generate personalized training recommendations based on employee profiles
Analyze segmentation effectiveness for training optimization
Prerequisites
Basic Python programming knowledge (functions, dictionaries, lists)
Understanding of CSV file operations
Familiarity with cybersecurity concepts
Text editor or Python IDE access
