Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: CSV file not found errors

Solution: Ensure scripts run in correct order (data generator first)
Verify current directory contains generated files
Issue: Risk scores all zero or incorrect

Solution: Check risk calculation logic in employee_data_generator.py
Verify all factors (access level, training history, incidents) are considered
Issue: Messages not personalized

Solution: Review determine_message_category() logic
Ensure employee attributes are correctly accessed
Issue: Empty segment files

Solution: Verify segmentation thresholds are appropriate
Check that employees exist in each category
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated practical audience segmentation for cybersecurity training programs. Students implemented Python-based segmentation using multiple criteria (role, location, risk factors) and applied the AIDA model to create targeted, personalized training messages.

Key takeaways:

Segmentation improves training relevance and effectiveness
Risk-based prioritization ensures critical personnel receive immediate attention
AIDA model structures persuasive communication for behavior change
Data-driven analysis enables continuous improvement of training programs
These techniques apply broadly to security awareness programs, compliance training, and organizational communication strategies. The segmentation approach scales to larger organizations and can incorporate additional factors like compliance status, geographic regulations, or business unit requirements.
